# Commands
## 1. To build image
docker build -t greet-app:1.0 .

## 2. To list images locally
docker image ls

## 3. To Run container with image
docker run -d --name=greet-app -p 8080:8080 greet-app:1.0

## 4. To Run container  with image and set cpu and memory limit
docker run -d --name=greet-app --cpus="1.5" --memory="512m" -p 8080:8080 greet-app:1.0

## COPY vs ADD
COPY - use it to copy the file present in local
ADD - If any tar file or present in remote location use ADD

Recommended is COPY incase if files present remote user wget command to download. (ADD is not Recommended practice it does not check integrity)

## CMD vs ENTRYPOINT
CMD - If you want to overwrite during runtime, Example: in docker file "/app/greet.py" mentioned can be overwrite with "/app/app.py"
ENTRYPOINT - If your application must be always with "/app/greet.py" or fixed start behaviour use ENTRYPOINT

## commnd to check docker networks
docker network ls

## command to check volumes
docker volume ls

## comman to login to container
docker exec -it <container id or name> bash

## How to check cpu and memory limit set to container. Login to container and run the below commands
cat /sys/fs/cgroup/cpu.max
cat /sys/fs/cgroup/memory.max